<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-11T06:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-11T06:35:00-05:00" n="587" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/892: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ford</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-11T15:00:00+03:25">November
                                    11, 1943—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 11—1:24 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1056. Medjliss today passed income tax project in its entirety and while
                            a few minor changes were made Millspaugh states that on the whole it is
                            acceptable. He said [<hi rend="italic">asked?</hi>] that departure of
                            Shields, Hurst and Breitenbach be expedited.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>